Package: miCCI
Title: Charlson Comorbidity Index Estimation from Anonymized ICD-10 Codes
Version: 0.4.3
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gaetan", "Kamdje Wabo",
           email  = "gaetan.kamdjewabo@medma.uni-heidelberg.de",
           role   = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Nandhini", "Santhanam",   role = "aut"),
    person("Piotr",  "Sokolowski",  role = "aut"),
    person("Thomas", "Ganslandt",   role = "aut"),
    person("Fabian", "Siegel",      role = "aut"))
Description: Six validated computational strategies for reconstructing the
    Charlson Comorbidity Index (CCI) from 3-character truncated ICD-10
    codes, as mandated by EU Genaral Data Protection Regulations.
    Strategies range from a fully deterministic interval estimator (S1) through
    probabilistic expected-value estimation (S2), multiple imputation (S3),
    Bayesian Dirichlet inference (S4), XGBoost machine learning (S5), to a
    Non-Negative Least Squares ensemble meta-learner (S6).
    Reference frequencies come from the German Federal Statistical Office
    (Destatis 23131-01). The Charlson mapping follows Quan et al. (2005)
    <doi:10.1097/01.mlr.0000182534.19832.83>.
